    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 11 altitude points (0-1000 km) with six compositional variables. Synthetic data follows atmospheric physics principles: surface-level N\u2082/O\u2082 dominance (\u03bc=78/21, \u03c3=1.2), thermospheric atomic oxygen peak (\u03bc=59\u00b125), and exospheric light gas (He/H) prevalence. Data exhibits inverse logistic decay for heavy gases and sigmoidal growth for light elements. The areaspline format maximizes data-ink ratio by using color-filled areas rather than separate legend markers. Cairo's principles are applied through luminance-ordered colors (surface gases lighter) and proportional stacking for part-to-whole relationships. Opacity settings (0.6) enable layer identification while maintaining vertical summation clarity. Tooltip design follows Tufte's minimalism with direct labeling and removal of decorative elements."
